{"questionId":"22441608","questionHtml":"<p>The gradient of the <strong>normal</strong> to the curve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></math> at the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>Calculate the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> (seen at any stage of their work)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>M1</em></strong> for an attempt to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> and their gradient into their derivative&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p>substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> into original equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p>\n<p>solving equations&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>11</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>, gives <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>43</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math> award <em><strong>A0M1A1M1M1A0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>For the final <em><strong>A</strong></em> marks, award at most <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em> if correct values are unlabelled or incorrectly labelled.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22441608","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.10","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"The gradient of the normal to the curve y=ax2+bx-10 at the point T2, 4 is -13. Calculate the value of a and the value of b.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"10","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}